Oasis star Bonehead has announced he is being treated for tonsil cancer. The musician Paul Arthurs, 56, addressed fans in a statement on Twitter and Instagram today.    He wrote: “Just to let you all know I'm going to be taking a break from playing for a while. “I have been diagnosed with tonsil cancer. “But the good news is it's treatable and I will be starting a course of treatment soon. “I will keep you posted how it is going,” he added.    Paul’s Oasis bandmate Liam Gallagher sent his love to the star following the news of his diagnosis. He wrote: “Sending BIG love to the 1 n only Bonehead and his family.    “Wishing you a speedy recovery we’re all thinking of you rasta you’ll be back on stage before you can say r we doing Colombia LG x.” (sic) Erasure’s Andy Bell also commented on Bonehead’s Twitter post, writing: “Get well soon Bone.” His other fans also took to the comments sections to send out messages of love and support. Angela Redshaw penned: “We will always support you bonehead you’re a legend. I will pray for you always.” READ MORE... Dan Walker on 'intense' new show debut after BBC Breakfast exit news [NEWS] Jane McDonald receives marriage proposal on same day as co-star [LATEST] Johnny Depp breaks down in court over harrowing audio clip [UPDATE]        Nigel wrote: “No way man, my wife has just had two years of treatment/surgeries for bowel/liver/lung cancer. “She is in remission now and getting better so stay strong you can get through this and def not on your own! Matthew Black commented: “Get well soon Bonehead take care of yourself. See you back on stage soon.” Matt Turner added: “So sorry to hear this Paul. Keep strong and i wish you a quickest recovery possible, everyone is with you.”      Paul is co-founder of legendary rock band Oasis and is best known for playing rhythm guitar and keyboard. He is credited for having played piano and mellotron on the band’s iconic album (What's the Story) Morning Glory? Oasis were an English rock band formed in Manchester in 1991. The band initially consisted of Liam (lead vocals, tambourine), Paul (guitar), Paul McGuigan (bass guitar) and Tony McCarroll (drums), before Liam's older brother Noel (lead guitar, vocals) joined as a fifth member.   